      {
        "introduction": "Isaiah takes time out from his public preaching to bring a special message to just one man. It is not known fully why Shebna is singled out, but his breach of trust in ordering his own burial sepulcher while serving as master of Hezekiah's household will cause his demotion to a lesser rank. The historical record will soon confirm his replacement by Eliakim, just as Isaiah now prophesies."
      },
